explanation: This problem can be solved using dynamic programming. We create a 2D dp array where dp[i][j] represents the minimum number of turns needed to print the substring s[i...j]. We fill the dp array in a bottom-up manner, considering two cases: when the characters at positions i and j are the same, and when they are different. When they are different, we try to split the substring s[i...j] into two parts at each position k and take the minimum number of turns.

